**SLIDE 13 — Rollout Plan**

*"So here is the plan. Three months — August, September, October. August is about setup and foundations — environment configuration, onboarding developers, training sessions, and a pilot scan on our highest-risk repositories. September is about expanding — reviewing the initial findings, tuning the rules, and running the full scan across all repositories. October is about operationalising it — triaging findings, setting up the remediation tracking workflow, and establishing the reporting dashboard as a permanent view for leadership. This is not a big bang implementation. It's a structured, phased rollout that starts generating value from week one.*

*And I want to leave you with one final thought. I've spoken to other interns on revenue-generating projects here. They're doing important work. But the code and data powering those projects has vulnerabilities that nobody is currently catching. The revenue those projects generate means nothing if a breach wipes it out — and then some. You don't just need the project management intern and the data analytics intern. You need the security intern working alongside them.*

*That's the ask. Thank you."*
